            <span></span>
            <span></span>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
    <Breadcrumbs
        items={[
            { label: 'Home', url: '/' },
            { label: 'Projects', url: '/projects' },
            { label: 'Brunno Rodrigues', url: '/projects/brunno-rodrigues' }
        ]}
    />

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="case-study-hero">
        <div class="case-study-hero-content">
            <div class="case-study-tag">Landing Page</div>
            <h1>Brunno Rodrigues</h1>
            <p class="case-study-subtitle">Professional landing page for massage therapist with clear booking CTAs and mobile-first design</p>

            <div class="case-study-meta">
                <div class="meta-item">
                    <span class="meta-label">Client</span>
                    <span class="meta-value">Brunno Rodrigues</span>
                </div>
                <div class="meta-item">
                    <span class="meta-label">Industry</span>
                    <span class="meta-value">Massage Therapy</span>
                </div>
                <div class="meta-item">
                    <span class="meta-label">Location</span>
                    <span class="meta-value">Porto, Portugal</span>
                </div>
                <div class="meta-item">
                    <span class="meta-label">Timeline</span>
                    <span class="meta-value">2 weeks</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="results-banner">
                <div class="result-card">
                    <div class="result-value">2 weeks</div>
                    <div class="result-label">Delivery Time</div>
                </div>
                <div class="result-card">
                    <div class="result-value">100%</div>
                    <div class="result-label">Mobile Optimized</div>
                </div>
                <div class="result-card">
                    <div class="result-value">SEO</div>
                    <div class="result-label">Ready</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="case-study-hero-image">
            <img src="/brunno-rodrigues.svg" alt="Brunno Rodrigues landing page preview">
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Brunno Rodrigues is a certified massage therapist and physiotherapist offering specialized massage services including sports massage, deep tissue, and therapeutic treatments. He needed a professional online presence to attract new clients and make booking easy.</p>

        <p>The challenge was creating a landing page that would establish credibility, clearly communicate his services, and convert visitors into bookings—all within a tight 2-week timeline and budget-friendly price point.</p>

        <p>The result is a clean, conversion-focused landing page that highlights his expertise, showcases his services, and makes booking a session as simple as one click.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Challenge Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>The Challenge</h2>

        <div class="challenge-content">
            <h3>The Situation</h3>
            <p>Brunno faced several common challenges for solo practitioners:</p>

            <ul class="challenge-list">
                <li><strong>No Online Presence:</strong> Relying entirely on Instagram and word-of-mouth referrals, missing potential clients searching online for massage services.</li>
                <li><strong>Booking Friction:</strong> Clients had to DM on Instagram or call, creating unnecessary friction in the booking process.</li>
                <li><strong>Lack of Credibility Signals:</strong> No professional website to showcase credentials, certifications, or client testimonials.</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile-First Audience:</strong> Most potential clients would discover him on mobile devices, requiring a mobile-optimized experience.</li>
                <li><strong>Tight Budget:</strong> As a solo practitioner, needed an affordable solution that still looked professional.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Goals</h3>
            <ul class="goals-list">
                <li>Create a professional landing page within 2 weeks</li>
                <li>Make booking process as simple as possible</li>
                <li>Showcase services and expertise clearly</li>
                <li>Optimize for mobile users (primary audience)</li>
                <li>Include basic SEO for local discoverability</li>
                <li>Stay within landing page budget (€500-800)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Solution Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>The Solution</h2>

        <h3>Discovery & Strategy</h3>
        <p>I started by researching Brunno's target audience and competitors. Most massage therapists in Porto had outdated websites or relied solely on social media. This was an opportunity to stand out with a modern, professional landing page.</p>

        <p>The strategy focused on three key principles:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Clarity over complexity:</strong> Single-page design with clear sections for services, about, and contact</li>
            <li><strong>Trust building:</strong> Prominent display of certifications, experience, and professional photos</li>
            <li><strong>Conversion optimization:</strong> Multiple CTAs strategically placed throughout the page</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Design Process</h3>

        <div class="implementation-phase">
            <h4>Week 1: Design & Content</h4>
            <p>Focused on creating a clean, professional design that would work perfectly on mobile:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Wireframing:</strong> Mapped out user journey from landing to booking</li>
                <li><strong>Visual Design:</strong> Clean, minimal aesthetic with calming colors (blues and whites)</li>
                <li><strong>Professional Photography:</strong> Worked with Brunno to get proper photos of his treatment room</li>
                <li><strong>Content Strategy:</strong> Wrote concise, benefit-focused copy for each service</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile-First Approach:</strong> Designed for mobile screens first, then adapted for desktop</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="implementation-phase">
            <h4>Week 2: Development & Launch</h4>
            <p>Built the landing page with modern web technologies for speed and reliability:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Development:</strong> Built with Astro for maximum performance (sub-1s load times)</li>
                <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Perfect display on all device sizes</li>
                <li><strong>Contact Integration:</strong> Multiple contact options (WhatsApp, phone, email)</li>
                <li><strong>SEO Setup:</strong> Meta tags, schema markup, and sitemap submission</li>
                <li><strong>Testing:</strong> Thorough testing across devices and browsers</li>
                <li><strong>Training:</strong> Taught Brunno how to update content himself</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Features Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>Key Features</h2>

        <h3>Clear Service Presentation</h3>
        <p>Each massage service has its own section with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Service name and description</li>
            <li>Duration and pricing</li>
            <li>Benefits and what to expect</li>
            <li>Direct booking CTA</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Professional Credentials</h3>
        <p>Established trust with prominent display of:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Professional certifications and training</li>
            <li>Years of experience</li>
            <li>Specializations (sports massage, deep tissue)</li>
            <li>Professional association memberships</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Multiple Contact Options</h3>
        <p>Made booking effortless with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>WhatsApp Button:</strong> One-click to start conversation</li>
            <li><strong>Click-to-Call:</strong> Direct phone calling on mobile</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Form:</strong> Simple form for those who prefer email</li>
            <li><strong>Location Map:</strong> Embedded Google Maps for easy navigation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>
        <p>Perfect mobile experience with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Touch-friendly buttons and navigation</li>
            <li>Fast loading on mobile networks (under 1 second)</li>
            <li>Readable typography without zooming</li>
            <li>Optimized images that load quickly</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Basic SEO Foundation</h3>
        <p>Set up for local discoverability:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Optimized title and meta descriptions</li>
            <li>LocalBusiness schema markup</li>
            <li>Fast page speed (crucial for SEO)</li>
            <li>Mobile-friendly (Google's #1 ranking factor)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Results Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Results</h2>

        <h3>Project Delivery</h3>
        <div class="results-grid">
            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Timeline</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Delivered on time</strong> - exactly 2 weeks from start to launch</li>
                    <li><strong>3 revision rounds</strong> included in timeline</li>
                    <li><strong>Same-day fixes</strong> for post-launch adjustments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Technical Performance</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>98/100 PageSpeed</strong> score on mobile</li>
                    <li><strong>0.8s load time</strong> on 4G connection</li>
                    <li><strong>100% mobile-friendly</strong> per Google's test</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="result-item">
                <div class="result-category">Client Impact</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Professional credibility</strong> - clients mention finding website</li>
                    <li><strong>Booking simplicity</strong> - one-click WhatsApp booking</li>
                    <li><strong>Self-manageable</strong> - Brunno can update content independently</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>What the Client Said</h3>
        <blockquote class="testimonial">
            <p>"Luís delivered exactly what I needed in the timeline promised. The website looks professional and many clients mention they found it easy to book through. Having a proper website instead of just Instagram has definitely helped me attract more serious clients."</p>
            <cite>— Brunno Rodrigues, Massage Therapist</cite>
        </blockquote>
    </section>

    <!-- Technologies Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section gray-bg">
        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <ul class="tech-list">
            <li><strong>Astro:</strong> Static site generator for maximum performance</li>
            <li><strong>CSS3:</strong> Modern CSS for responsive design</li>
            <li><strong>Google Maps API:</strong> Location integration</li>
            <li><strong>Schema.org:</strong> LocalBusiness structured data</li>
            <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Fast content delivery</li>
            <li><strong>Formspree:</strong> Contact form handling</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Lessons Learned Section -->
    <section class="case-study-section">
        <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
        <p>This project reinforced several key principles for landing page projects:</p>

        <ol class="lessons-list">
            <li><strong>Simplicity wins:</strong> A well-executed single-page design beats a complex multi-page site every time for solo practitioners.</li>
            <li><strong>Mobile-first is non-negotiable:</strong> 85% of Brunno's visitors are on mobile. Designing mobile-first ensured the best experience for the majority.</li>
            <li><strong>Multiple contact options matter:</strong> Different people prefer different contact methods. Offering WhatsApp, phone, and email maximizes conversion.</li>
            <li><strong>Speed builds trust:</strong> A fast-loading page immediately signals professionalism and quality.</li>
            <li><strong>Clear CTAs drive action:</strong> Strategically placed "Book Now" buttons throughout the page make the desired action obvious.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Section -->
    <section class="cta-section">
        <h2>NEED A LANDING PAGE?</h2>
        <p>If you're a solo practitioner or small business looking for a professional, conversion-focused landing page delivered quickly, I can help.</p>
        <a href="/#contact" class="btn-primary">GET YOUR LANDING PAGE</a>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Projects Section -->
    <section class="related-projects">
        <h2>Related Projects</h2>
        <div class="related-projects-grid">
            <a href="/projects/porto-massage-studio" class="related-project-card">
                <img src="/porto-massage-studio.svg" alt="Porto Massage Studio website">
                <h3>Porto Massage Studio</h3>
                <p>Landing page for massage studio</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/projects/porto-car-care" class="related-project-card">
                <img src="/final fnal final.svg" alt="Porto Car Care website">
                <h3>Porto Car Care</h3>
                <p>Local SEO case study with 3× visibility growth</p>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <script>
        // Mobile Menu Toggle
        const mobileMenuToggle = document.querySelector('.mobile-menu-toggle');
        const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');

        if (mobileMenuToggle) {
            mobileMenuToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
                mobileMenuToggle.classList.toggle('active');
                navLinks.classList.toggle('active');
            });

            const links = navLinks.querySelectorAll('a');
            links.forEach(link => {
                link.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    mobileMenuToggle.classList.remove('active');
                    navLinks.classList.remove('active');
                });
            });
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>

<style>
/* Reset & Base Styles */
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

:root {
    --color-bg: #0d0d0d;
